                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241028-61-victim619 t18241028-61-viclabel332"></join>, Minories. On the 11th of October, I was in the shop, and heard a noise at the door; I ran out and saw the prisoner crossing the road with this paper under his arm, which I had placed near the door; he sat down on a street door, and put it behind him - but seeing me, he got up and ran off, leaving it there - I pursued and brought him back; the prisoner was brought into the shop.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was running on an errand; the gentleman took hold of me, and found the paper on the step; he said the boy who took it had run off, but that I was with him.</p>
